  "response": "Here are some tips to prepare for 10th board exams:\n\n1. Study Plan\n- Create a structured timetable\n- Allocate time for each subject\n- Include breaks and revision time\n- Set realistic goals\n\n2. Subject-wise Preparation\n- Mathematics: Practice lots of problems\n- Science: Focus on concepts and diagrams\n- Social Science: Make notes and timelines\n- Languages: Read and practice grammar\n\n3. Study Techniques\n- Use NCERT textbooks as primary reference\n- Make concise notes\n- Use mind maps and flowcharts\n- Practice previous years' question papers\n- Take mock tests\n\n4. Time Management\n- Start studying early\n- Avoid last-minute cramming\n- Prioritize difficult subjects\n- Regular revision\n- Practice time-bound problem solving\n\n5. Additional Tips\n- Stay physically and mentally healthy\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Eat nutritious food\n- Stay calm and confident\n- Minimize distractions\n- Use online resources for help\n\n6. Exam Preparation\n- Understand exam pattern\n- Know marking scheme\n- Learn time management during exam\n- Practice solving papers within time limit\n- Keep necessary stationery ready\n\n7. Seek Help\n- Consult teachers\n- Join study groups\n- Take coaching if needed\n\nConsistency and focused preparation are key to success.",
